data.content: The MSK APP Oncology Fellowship is designed to bridge the gap between APP graduate education and the knowledge and skills required for clinical practice in the specialized field of oncology. This program was built to provide a supportive transition to APP practice with the goal of producing graduates who are skilled, confident, and compassionate healthcare providers equipped to excel in the complex field of oncology. The MSK APP Oncology Fellowship program is accredited with distinction by APPFA which stands for Advanced Practice Provider Fellowship Accreditation—and MSK was the first program to ever earn APPFA accreditation! During the fellowship year, fellows complete rotations to various different clinical areas related to their clinical subspecialty. Fellows participate in didactic and experiential learning sessions and also have the ability to refine their professional presentation skills throughout the year. The fellowship runs for 12 months, with the exception of the Hospice and Palliative Care subspecialty which runs for 15 months. We typically accept 15-20 fellows per year. The stipend is $100,000 for the 12-month program and $125,000 for the 15-month Hospice & Palliative Care track. Fellows primarily work at our Main Hospital at 1275 York Avenue in the Upper East Side neighborhood of New York City, though some rotations may occur at regional sites. Fellows generally work about 50 hours per week with 40 hours focused on patient care in either inpatient or outpatient rotations and 10 hours for didactic learning. Schedules can vary depending on the subspecialty and clinical needs, and fellows may be asked to work nights, weekends, or holidays. Does that all sound good?
